<exercise checkit-seed="0008" checkit-slug="D4" checkit-title="Binomial Distribution">
  <statement>
      
      
      <p>
          Suppose a group of adults are selected as test subjects for a study.  Each of the  <m>7</m>  people has a <m>0.2</m> chance of  having some type of phobia.  Suppose that whether or not each  person  have some type of phobia is independent of the other  people.  Find the following:
      </p>
      
      
      <p>
          <ol>
              <li>
                  What is the probability that <m>6</m>  people  have some type of phobia?
              </li>
             
              <li>
                  What is the probability that <m>7</m>  people  have some type of phobia?
              </li>
              
              
              <li>
                  What is the probability that  at most  <m>6</m>  people  have some type of phobia?
              </li>
              
              <li>
                  What is the probability that between <m>1</m> and <m>6</m> (inclusive)  people  have some type of phobia?
              </li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
      
      
     
      
          
          
          
          
      
  </statement>
